sta-article__url-stepper"><span class="kasta-breadcrumbs"><span class="kasta-breadcrumbs__path"><a class="" href="/">Home / </a><a aria-current="page" class="active" href="/blog">Blog / </a></span><span class="kasta-breadcrumbs__tail">How to Send Bitcoin: A Step-by-Step Guide</span></span></div><div class="kasta-article__date-reading"><span>June 17, 2022</span><span class="circle"></span><span>3 min read</span></div><h1 class="kasta-article__name">How to Send Bitcoin: A Step-by-Step Guide</h1><p>With the Kasta app, sending Bitcoins (BTC) to other users is fast, easy, and secure. All you need is a verified Kasta account and a QR code or phone number of the recipient to proceed with the transaction.</p><p>If it’s your first time using Kasta and you want to know how to send Bitcoin to another person using the app, keep reading as we’ve got all the information you need in this blog post. You’re welcome!</p><p class="kasta-article__text">But First, What is the Kasta App? </p><p>Kasta is an easy-to-use crypto payment app. It helps people transition into a crypto-based economy by simplifying the process of using crypto for payments and remittances. The app allows you to<a href="/"> send crypto</a> and receive them instantly in just a few clicks, without tricky processes that involve long wallet addresses, network types, memo IDs, or high transaction fees. </p><p>The first version of the app only accepts cryptocurrencies. But the team is already developing the second version of the app, which will also allow you to send and receive payments in fiat currencies such as Euro and US Dollar.</p><p class="kasta-article__text">Who Can Open a Kasta Account? </p><p>Users who are at least 18 years old, are able to provide identification documents and proof of address, and are able to form a binding contract under applicable laws in your domestic legislation can open a Kasta account.</p><p class="kasta-article__text">An Easy Guide on How to Send Someone Bitcoin </p><section class="kasta-article__guide"><p>Here’s the end-to-end process of sending BTC to another Kasta user:</p><ol><li><span>1. Create a Kasta account.</span><div class="kasta-article__guide__wrapper-lazy-image"><div class="kasta-image kasta-image--high-loaded kasta-article__guide__img" style="padding-bottom: 86.0835%;"><img src="article-page/how-to-send-bitcoin-1.png" class="kasta-image__img kasta-image__img--high"></div></div><ol><li>Download the Kasta app from the App Store or Play Store.</li><li>Open the app and sign up using your mobile number, email address, name, and home address.</li><li>Set up your pin code.</li><li>Complete two levels of Know Your Customer (KYC) verifications by providing a valid ID and proof of residency. KYC is a part of a due diligence process that aims to prevent money laundering, terrorist financing, corruption, and fraud.</li></ol></li><li><span>2. Add Bitcoin into your account.</span><div class="kasta-article__guide__wrapper-lazy-image"><div class="kasta-image kasta-article__guide__img" style="padding-bottom: 67.3349%;"></div></div><ol><li>Log in to your Kasta account.</li><li>Enter the verification code sent to your mobile number.</li><li>On the dashboard, click the “Add Funds” button.</li><li>Click “Deposit from a wallet.”</li><li>Choose Bitcoin.</li><li>Copy the address to receive Bitcoin from an external wallet.</li><li>On the external wallet, click to withdraw Bitcoin, paste the address, double check, and proceed.</li><li>Otherwise, you can buy Bitcoin using a credit or debit card by clicking “Buy with card.”</li></ol></li><li><span>3. Send Bitcoin to another user.</span><div class="kasta-article__guide__wrapper-lazy-image"><div class="kasta-image kasta-article__guide__img" style="padding-bottom: 35.2442%;"></div></div><ol><li>On the dashboard, click the “Send” button.</li><li>Enter the phone number that the recipient used to sign up in Kasta, or scan their Kasta QR code.</li><li>Choose Bitcoin and enter the amount you’d like to send.</li><li>Double-check the information, and then enter your pin code to confirm.</li><li>The transaction receipt will appear.</li></ol></li></ol></section><p class="kasta-article__text">How Much are Crypto Transfer Fees? </p><p>The good news is that in Kasta, you can send BTC to another user free of charge. There are no gas fees or transaction fees, and the other user would receive the payment instantly even if they’re located in a different country.</p><p>It’s good to note though that the recipient has the choice to receive your payment in their preferred currency, but with minimal conversion fees. Therefore, if you prefer to pay in BTC but they want to receive payments in USDT, they can enable the Easy Swap Engine feature to automatically convert BTC to USDT on their behalf. Fees are charged in the source currency. Therefore, if you send someone BTC and they receive it in USDT, the fee will be charged in BTC.</p><p class="kasta-article__text">How to Transfer Bitcoins Between Wallets </p><p>Users can securely build their Bitcoin portfolio in Kasta. The process of depositing Bitcoin into Kasta is already mentioned above, but if you want to withdraw your assets and move them to another wallet, you can easily do so in just a few steps.</p><ol class=""><li>On the dashboard, under assets, click “Bitcoin.”</li><li>Click the “Withdraw” button.</li><li>Enter the wallet address, double-check, and click next.</li><li>Enter the amount you’d like to withdraw, double-check, and then proceed.</li><li>Enter your pin code to confirm.</li><li>The transaction receipt will appear.</li></ol><p class="kasta-article__text">Aside From Bitcoin, Which Cryptocurrencies are Accepted on the App? </p><p>As of writing, the Kasta app also accepts Ethereum (ETH), Tether (USDT), and the <a href="/token">KASTA token</a>, but we’re also looking forward to accepting more tokens and fiat currencies in the future. We will put out an announcement as soon as we’ve added more currencies to the app.</p><p class="kasta-article__text">Will I Be Able to View My Transaction History in the App? </p><p>Yes. You can view your transaction history when you click the lower rightmost icon on the dashboard. You can also sort the history based on the type of transaction (sent, received, deposit, withdraw, swap, and rewards).</p><p class="kasta-article__text">Is it Safe to Use the App? </p><p>Kasta follows thorough KYC processes and anti-money laundering (AML) guidelines to verify individuals and protect its users against fraud, money laundering, and other illegal activities. We also have two-factor authentication. To be able to log in, we need to verify your phone number with a verification code, and you cannot complete a transaction without correctly entering your pin code.</p><p class="kasta-article__text">Do You Have Customer Support? </p><p>Yes. We have live chat support in the app. Please don’t hesitate to reach out if you have questions or concerns with your transactions.</p><div class="kasta-article__recomended-by-kasta"><p>Recommended by Kasta</p><a aria-current="page" class="recomended-cards__link active" href="/blog">Check more posts</a></div></div><div class="kasta-cookie-banner"><div class="kasta-cookie-banner__text">We use cookies to enhance your experience and analyze our site usage. Please see our <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a> for more information.</div><div class="kasta-cookie-banner__buttons"><button class="kasta-button kasta-button--outline" type="button">Accept</button><button class="kasta-button kasta-button--outline" type="button">Close</button></div></div><footer class="kasta-footer"><div class="kasta-footer__logo"><a aria-label="Home" class="" href="/"><svg width="130" height="36" viewBox="0 0 130 36" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M38.31 10.057c-9.033 0-13.234 7.168-13.234 13.024 0 9.243 7.037 12.866 11.948 12.866 6.748 0 8.402-5.067 8.402-5.067v4.516h6.04V22.004s-.447-11.947-13.156-11.947Zm.053 19.746c-3.571 0-6.46-3.02-6.46-6.